#: ../../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/metadata.rst:92
msgid ""
"calibre can store any number of extra data files associated with a book. "
"These can be alternate covers, supplementary material, etc. They cannot be "
"viewed directly or used as conversion sources. Nor are they indexed by the "
"Full text search engine in calibre. To view/add/delete them select the book "
"and right click the :guilabel:`Edit metadata` button and choose "
":guilabel:`Manage data files`. This will pop-up a window where you can "
"perform operations on these files. Alternately, you can right click the "
":guilabel:`Add books` button and choose :guilabel:`Add data files to "
"selected book records` to more quickly add data files."
msgstr ""
